decks.notes: The deck focuses on utilizing artifacts and mana ramp to quickly assemble a powerful combo involving Mystic Forge and various other pieces. It aims to generate significant card advantage and mana efficiency through multiple artifacts such as Grim Monolith and Lotus Petal. Additionally, it includes disruption elements like Pithing Needle and Soul-Guide Lantern to disrupt opponents' strategies. The ultimate goal is to create a dominant board presence and overwhelm opponents with a strong combination of cards and abilities, ultimately leading to victory through a powerful and synergistic combo.

The deck focuses on assembling key artifacts like Mystic Forge and The One Ring to generate infinite mana and card advantage. By combining artifacts such as Voltaic Key, Basalt Monolith, and Grim Monolith, the deck can create powerful synergies that allow for explosive plays. The inclusion of Tezzeret, Cruel Captain and Karn, the Great Creator provide additional utility and disruption to control the game. With the ability to tutor and search for artifacts utilizing Urza's Saga, Urza's Tower, and Urza's Workshop, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a fast and resilient combo strategy.

This deck focuses on using powerful graveyard-based spells like Reanimate and Entomb to quickly bring back powerful creatures like Archon of Cruelty and Murktide Regent. The deck also includes disruptive elements like Thoughtseize and Force of Will to protect the combo pieces and disrupt the opponent's game plan. Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student helps filter through the deck to find key pieces, while Atraxa, Grand Unifier provides additional value by pumping up the team. The deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces and overwhelm the opponent before they have a chance to respond.

The main focus of this deck is to quickly deploy threats and disrupt opponents with counterspells and removal. Utilizing cheap cantrips like Brainstorm and Ponder to dig for key cards, the deck aims to apply pressure early with efficient creatures like Dragon's Rage Channeler and Cori-Steel Cutter. By using Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student and Murktide Regent to generate card advantage, the deck can maintain aggression while also controlling the game through countermagic and burn spells like Lightning Bolt. The mana base is streamlined to ensure consistency in casting spells and disrupting opponents' strategies.

The main focus of this Dragon Stompy deck is to quickly disrupt and control the opponent's resources with cards like Chalice of the Void, Blood Moon, and Magus of the Moon, while using aggressive creatures and powerful burn spells to end the game quickly. The deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with early pressure and lock them out of casting their spells effectively, ultimately securing a victory through a combination of fast creatures and direct damage.

The main concept of this deck is to quickly and efficiently dump your entire library into the graveyard, using cards like Balustrade Spy and Undercity Informer, to win the game with Thassa's Oracle or Goblin Charbelcher. The deck aims to go off as fast as possible and disrupt opponents with disruptive spells like Cabal Therapy and Thoughtseize. It heavily relies on using mana acceleration cards like Simian Spirit Guide and Lotus Petal to cast multiple spells in a single turn and win the game before the opponent has a chance to react.

This deck focuses on using a combination of control elements such as counterspells and removal spells to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The main win condition revolves around playing Phyrexian Dreadnought, a powerful creature that can be cheated into play with the help of spells like Consign to Memory. The deck also includes cards like Torpor Orb and Dress Down to shut down opposing strategies that rely on enter the battlefield triggers. Overall, the goal is to control the game until the key combo pieces can be assembled to secure a victory.

The deck focuses on quickly filling up the graveyard with powerful creatures through cards like Entomb and Thoughtseize, then utilizing reanimation spells like Reanimate and Animate Dead to bring them back into play for a quick victory. It also includes disruptive elements like Force of Will and Daze to protect the combo. Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student provides card advantage and selection, while cards like Brazen Borrower and Archon of Cruelty offer additional threats and control options. The deck aims to efficiently assemble its combo pieces and disrupt the opponent's game plan to secure a win.

This Dimir Tempo deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's plays using cards like Thoughtseize and Daze, while maintaining card advantage with cards like Mishra's Bauble and Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student. The deck aims to control the game tempo by efficiently casting spells with cards like Brainstorm and Ponder, while also dealing with threats using removal spells like Fatal Push. Murktide Regent and Brazen Borrower provide finisher options, while Nethergoyf and Orcish Bowmasters provide threats and additional disruption. The mana base is built around efficient fetch lands and Underground Sea to support the deck's game plan.

This deck focuses on creating a resource imbalance by disrupting the opponent's hand and board presence, while also controlling the game through cards like Smallpox and Liliana of the Veil. It utilizes land destruction and creature removal to keep the opponent on the back foot, while also employing cards like Ensnaring Bridge and Karn, the Great Creator to further hinder their game plan. The deck also has tools to generate value and protect itself, such as Retrofitter Foundry and Bitter Triumph. Overall, the strategy revolves around attrition and resource denial to secure victory.

The deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures like Dragon's Rage Channeler and Murktide Regent, combined with efficient spells like Lightning Bolt and Daze, to quickly deal damage while disrupting the opponent's game plan with cards like Wasteland and Force of Will. The deck also includes card draw and filtering (Preordain, Ponder, Brainstorm) to maintain a consistent game plan and keep up the pressure. Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student serves as card advantage and disruption, while Mishra's Bauble and Urza's Bauble provide additional card selection and synergies with other cards in the deck.

This deck focuses on utilizing aggressive creatures like Dragon's Rage Channeler and Murktide Regent to deal quick damage to the opponent. It also includes disruption spells like Daze, Force of Will, and Wasteland to control the board and protect the creatures. Additionally, the deck includes card draw and selection spells like Ponder, Preordain, and Mishra's Bauble to ensure card advantage and consistency. The inclusion of Tamiyo, Inquisitive Student adds a versatile threat to the deck. Overall, this deck aims to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and efficient aggro strategy.

The main concept of this deck is to establish control through a combination of powerful enchantments, removal spells, and disruptive creatures. The deck utilizes cards like Solitude, Swords to Plowshares, and Leyline Binding to control the board while also ramping up mana with cards like Utopia Sprawl and Serra's Sanctum. The addition of Yorion as a companion gives the deck additional value and consistency. Overall, the deck aims to outvalue and outlast opponents through a combination of control elements and resource management.

The main concept of this deck is to control the game by constantly disrupting the opponent's strategy with cards like Torpor Orb, Force of Will, and Dress Down. The deck aims to keep the opponent's creatures in check while building up its own board presence with creatures like Phyrexian Dreadnought and Nulldrifter. The deck also focuses on card advantage and manipulation through cards like Brainstorm, Ponder, and Stock Up. With its mix of control elements and threat base, this deck aims to outlast the opponent and secure victory through strategic gameplay.

The deck focuses on utilizing the combination of Mystic Forge, Manifold Key, and Voltaic Key to generate immense value and draw through the deck quickly. It aims to ramp up with mana acceleration, tutor for important pieces with Urza's Saga, and protect its game plan with Defense Grid. The deck's end goal is to assemble a powerful board state with Urza's Tower and Karn, the Great Creator, while using Planar Nexus and Kozilek's Command to disrupt the opponent's game plan. The primary win condition is to overwhelm the opponent with a strong board presence and efficient card advantage.

This deck focuses on using Life from the Loam to continuously recur key lands like Wasteland and Bojuka Bog, while utilizing cards like Smallpox and Thoughtseize to disrupt the opponent's game plan. It also has a win condition in Dark Depths combo, supported by cards like Thespian's Stage and Sylvan Library to help dig for pieces. The deck aims to control the game through resource denial and disruption, while also having a potential fast kill option with the Dark Depths combo.
